able to change their life.

11
00:00:53.153 --> 00:00:57.818
His story is forever carved
into the skyline of this city.

12
00:00:58.058 --> 00:01:00.789
A city he transformed
into his likeness.

13
00:01:04.765 --> 00:01:07.826
And I miss the man.

14
00:01:08.068 --> 00:01:10.264
I miss him.

15
00:01:10.304 --> 00:01:12.569
More than any amount
of words can say.

16
00:01:15.809 --> 00:01:17.641
His smile alone
would've washed away

17
00:01:17.678 --> 00:01:19.806
the silence that
fills this room.

18
00:01:23.283 --> 00:01:25.218
Finn Wallace.

19
00:01:29.489 --> 00:01:30.582
Dad.

20
00:01:33.193 --> 00:01:36.163
He believed in people.

21
00:01:36.196 --> 00:01:37.721
He believed in
giving opportunities

22
00:01:37.764 --> 00:01:40.199
to the disadvantaged.

23
00:01:40.233 --> 00:01:42.429
[Cellphone chimes]

24
00:01:42.469 --> 00:01:45.166
He gave.

25
00:01:45.205 --> 00:01:48.642
He supported.

26
00:01:48.675 --> 00:01:51.201
He did so much for all of us.

27
00:01:51.244 --> 00:01:53.543
[Whispering indistinctly]

28
00:01:53.580 --> 00:01:54.843
All of you.

29
00:01:54.881 --> 00:02:01.185
♪♪

30
00:02:01.221 --> 00:02:06.182
My father was taken from
us on the streets of London.

31
00:02:06.226 --> 00:02:09.458
And now London will deliver
to us those that took him.

32
00:02:09.496 --> 00:02:11.522
Finn Wallace.

33
00:02:11.565 --> 00:02:14.694
